   "source": [
    "# EXAONE-Deep-7.8B QLoRA Hyperparameter Optimization\n",
    "\n",
    "**Issue #67** — Systematic hyperparameter search to improve BLEU/ROUGE-L scores.\n",
    "\n",
    "| | BLEU | ROUGE-L |\n",
    "|---|---|---|\n",
    "| Baseline (EXP-001) | 17.32 | 18.28 |\n",
    "| Target | ≥ 30 | ≥ 40 |\n",
    "\n",
    "**Experiments:**\n",
    "- **EXP-002**: LoRA rank search (8, 32, 64)\n",
    "- **EXP-003**: Learning rate search (1e-4, 5e-5, 2e-4 linear)\n",
    "- **EXP-004**: Epoch exploration (2, 3 epochs)\n",
    "\n",
    "Runtime: **GPU (A100 or L4 recommended)**"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# 1. Install dependencies\n",
    "!pip install -q -U transformers==5.3.0 datasets accelerate peft bitsandbytes trl==0.12.0 wandb rouge-score python-dotenv"
   ],
   "execution_count": null,
   "outputs": []
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# 2. EXAONE transformers compatibility patch\n",
    "import os\n",
    "patch_path = \"/usr/local/lib/python3.12/dist-packages/transformers/utils/generic.py\"\n",
    "patch_code = \"\\ndef check_model_inputs(func):\\n    return func\\n\"\n",
    "\n",
    "if os.path.exists(patch_path):\n",
    "    with open(patch_path, \"r\") as f:\n",
    "        content = f.read()\n",
    "    if \"def check_model_inputs\" not in content:\n",
    "        with open(patch_path, \"a\") as f:\n",
    "            f.write(patch_code)\n",
    "        print(\"Transformers patched.\")\n",
    "    else:\n",
    "        print(\"Already patched.\")"
   ],
   "execution_count": null,
   "outputs": []
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# 3. Clone repo and set paths\n",
    "import os, sys\n",
    "\n",
    "REPO_URL = \"https://github.com/GovOn-Org/GovOn.git\"\n",
    "BRANCH = \"colab\"\n",
    "PROJECT_ROOT = \"/content/GovOn\"\n",
    "\n",
    "if not os.path.exists(PROJECT_ROOT):\n",
    "    !git clone -b {BRANCH} {REPO_URL} {PROJECT_ROOT}\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    !git -C {PROJECT_ROOT} pull origin {BRANCH}\n",
    "\n",
    "sys.path.insert(0, PROJECT_ROOT)\n",
    "os.environ[\"PROJECT_ROOT\"] = PROJECT_ROOT\n",
    "print(f\"Project root: {PROJECT_ROOT}\")"
   ],
   "execution_count": null,
   "outputs": []
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# 4. Authenticate W&B and HuggingFace\n",
    "import wandb\n",
    "from huggingface_hub import login as hf_login\n",
    "\n",
    "# W&B login\n",
    "WANDB_KEY = \"\"  # paste wandb key or set WANDB_API_KEY env var\n",
    "HF_TOKEN = \"\"   # paste HuggingFace token\n",
    "\n",
    "if WANDB_KEY:\n",
    "    wandb.login(key=WANDB_KEY)\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    wandb.login()  # prompts for key\n",
    "\n",
    "if HF_TOKEN:\n",
    "    hf_login(token=HF_TOKEN)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Authentication complete.\")"
   ],
   "execution_count": null,
   "outputs": []
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# 5. Verify data files exist\n",
    "import os\n",
    "PROJECT_ROOT = os.environ.get(\"PROJECT_ROOT\", \"/content/GovOn\")\n",
    "\n",
    "paths = {\n",
    "    \"train\": f\"{PROJECT_ROOT}/data/processed/civil_complaint_train.jsonl\",\n",
    "    \"val\":   f\"{PROJECT_ROOT}/data/processed/civil_complaint_val.jsonl\",\n",
    "    \"test\":  f\"{PROJECT_ROOT}/data/processed/civil_complaint_test.jsonl\",\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "for name, path in paths.items():\n",
    "    exists = os.path.exists(path)\n",
    "    size = os.path.getsize(path) // 1024 if exists else 0\n",
    "    print(f\"  {name}: {'✓' if exists else '✗'} {path} ({size} KB)\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Create output dirs\n",
    "os.makedirs(f\"{PROJECT_ROOT}/models/checkpoints\", exist_ok=True)\n",
    "os.makedirs(f\"{PROJECT_ROOT}/docs/outputs/experiments\", exist_ok=True)"
   ],
   "execution_count": null,
   "outputs": []
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Run All Experiments (EXP-002 ~ EXP-004)\n",
    "\n",
    "Runs all 8 hyperparameter configurations sequentially, logging each to W&B."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
